{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Agra: The Mughal&nbsp;Capital","content":"<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">When I looked at the <em>&#8216;darwaza&#8217;</em>,<em> </em>I felt as if the king was about to enter through it, riding a majestic horse, coming back victorious from a battle</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">&#8211; Dada</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Dada (my grandfather) often told me about Fatehpur Sikri and its grandeur. Occasionally, I used to think that he was exaggerating, but his descriptions never failed to pique my interest about the city-fort. Akbar&#8217;s reign is perhaps one of the few sections of my history book that I loved reading and the prospect of visiting his kingdom&#8217;s blooming capital was very exciting.<!--more--></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">After our splendid tour of the Taj Mahal, we had breakfast and Mr. Rupinder Singh (who was taking us to the various places) drove us towards Fatehpur Sikri. We boarded a bus from the car-parking area.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">When one of the several entrances became visible, Dada&#8217;s description came to my mind.</p>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2563\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2563\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/2016/02/08/agra-the-mughal-capital/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=424\" data-orig-size=\"1024,424\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;3.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446568997&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;18&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.005&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (9 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=424?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=424?w=700\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2563 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=424\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (9 of 18)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg 1024w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=150&amp;h=62 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=450&amp;h=186 450w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=768&amp;h=318 768w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-9-of-181.jpg?w=700&amp;h=290 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Fatehpur Sikri &#8211; the city outside the fort</figcaption></figure>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The city had been abandoned after 1585 due to the proximity of the Rajput neighbourhood and scarcity of water. It had remained a ghost town following the abandonment.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Now, however, it is one of the best-preserved elements of Mughal architecture.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Our time was limited (owing to our relatively late hour of visit), and we hired a guide who explained to us a few sections of the fort.</p>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2483\" style=\"width: 600px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2483\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600\" data-orig-size=\"600,600\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;5.6&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446563837&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;55&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.0025&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (1 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600?w=600\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2483 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (1 of 18)\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg 600w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=150&amp;h=150 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-1-of-18.jpg?w=450&amp;h=450 450w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">A segment of the Diwan-i-aam</figcaption></figure>\n<p>The above hoop was supposedly used as a tool for delivering capital punishment: an elephant used to be tethered to trample a criminal.</p>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2492\" style=\"width: 871px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2492\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=871&#038;h=600\" data-orig-size=\"871,600\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446564406&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;18&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.16666666666667&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (10 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=871&#038;h=600?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=871&#038;h=600?w=700\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2492 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=871&#038;h=600\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (10 of 18)\" width=\"871\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg 871w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=150&amp;h=103 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=450&amp;h=310 450w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=768&amp;h=529 768w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-10-of-18.jpg?w=700&amp;h=482 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 871px) 100vw, 871px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">The central pillar of Diwan-i-khas (hall of private audience) where Akbar used to be seated with the <em>navaratna </em>surrounding him</figcaption></figure>\n<p>The Diwan-i-khas is a simple square building. However it is famous for the central pillar.</p>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2559\" style=\"width: 570px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2559\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/2016/02/08/agra-the-mughal-capital/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=570&#038;h=600\" data-orig-size=\"570,600\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446564721&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;21&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.1&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (11 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=570&#038;h=600?w=428\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=570&#038;h=600?w=570\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2559 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=570&#038;h=600\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (11 of 18)\" width=\"570\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg 570w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=143&amp;h=150 143w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-11-of-181.jpg?w=428&amp;h=450 428w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">This pillar represents the <em>Dīn-i Ilāhī</em></figcaption></figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The <b>Dīn-i Ilāhī</b> (Persian: <span dir=\"rtl\" lang=\"fa\" xml:lang=\"fa\">دین الهی</span>‎‎ lit. &#8220;Religion of God&#8221;) was a syncretic religion propounded by the Mughal emperor Akbar the Great in 1582 AD, intending to merge the best elements of the religions of his empire, and thereby reconcile the differences that divided his subjects.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">-Wikipedia</p>\n</blockquote>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2477\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2477\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=420\" data-orig-size=\"1024,420\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;3.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446565635&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;18&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.001&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (13 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=420?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=420?w=700\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2477 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=420\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (13 of 18)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg 1024w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=150&amp;h=62 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=450&amp;h=185 450w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=768&amp;h=315 768w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-13-of-18.jpg?w=700&amp;h=287 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Pachisi </em>used to be played with sixteen young slaves wearing the players&#8217; colours, representing the pieces</figcaption></figure>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2557\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2557\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/2016/02/08/agra-the-mughal-capital/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=399\" data-orig-size=\"1024,399\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4.5&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446565807&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;36&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.01&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (15 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=399?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=399?w=700\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2557 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=399\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (15 of 18)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"399\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg 1024w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=150&amp;h=58 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=450&amp;h=175 450w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=768&amp;h=299 768w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-15-of-181.jpg?w=700&amp;h=273 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Platform inside the <em>Anup Talao. </em>Tansen would perform different <em>ragas </em>at different times of the day, seated on this platform.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2481\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2481\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=574\" data-orig-size=\"1024,574\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446565949&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;25&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.076923076923077&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (17 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=574?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=574?w=700\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2481 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=574\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (17 of 18)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"574\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg 1024w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=150&amp;h=84 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=450&amp;h=252 450w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=768&amp;h=431 768w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-17-of-18.jpg?w=700&amp;h=392 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Jahangir, Akbar&#8217;s son supposedly erased the faces of several works of art because he did not want to distinguish between them</figcaption></figure>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2554\" style=\"width: 600px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2554\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/2016/02/08/agra-the-mughal-capital/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600\" data-orig-size=\"600,600\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446566375&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;24&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.2&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fatehpur Sikri (2 of 18)\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600?w=450\" data-large-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600?w=600\" class=\" size-full wp-image-2554 aligncenter\" src=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=600&#038;h=600\" alt=\"Fatehpur Sikri (2 of 18)\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg 600w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=150&amp;h=150 150w, https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-2-of-181.jpg?w=450&amp;h=450 450w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">On the left is an elevated platform which used to be Akbar&#8217;s resting place. On the right is the dining area.</figcaption></figure>\n<figure data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_2564\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img data-attachment-id=\"2564\" data-permalink=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.wordpress.com/2016/02/08/agra-the-mughal-capital/fatehpur-sikri-4-of-18/\" data-orig-file=\"https://nabhoneelparchments.files.wordpress.com/2016/02/fatehpur-sikri-4-of-181.jpg?w=1024&#038;h=552\" data-orig-size=\"1024,552\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Nabhoneel Majumdar&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Canon EOS REBEL T3&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1446566904&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;24&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00625&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&